As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |access-date=January 31, 2008 |title=U.S. Census website }}</ref> of 2000, there were 179 people, 94 households, and 40 families residing in the town. The population density was {{convert|523.6|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}.  There were 147 housing units at an average density of {{convert|430.0|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the town was 92.74% [[White American|White]], 2.23% [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 0.56% [[Asian American|Asian]], 3.35% from [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census|other races]], and 1.12% from two or more races. [[Hispanics in the United States|Hispanics or Latinos]] of any race were 3.35% of the population.

There were 94 households, of which 18.1% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 37.2% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 2.1% had a female householder with no husband present, and 57.4% were non-families. 39.4% of all households were made up of individuals, and 1.1% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 1.90 and the average family size was 2.63.

The age distribution was 12.8% under the age of 18, 5.6% from 18 to 24, 53.1% from 25 to 44, 24.0% from 45 to 64, and 4.5% who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 37 years. For every 100 females, there were 132.5 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 140.0 males.

The median income for a household in the town was $41,563, and the median income for a family was $59,688. Males had a median income of $28,750 versus $26,563 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $25,165.  None of the families and 4.3% of the population were living below the [[poverty line]].
